The finalists of the women's US Open tennis championship, Leylah Fernandez and Emma Raducanu. 

Britain's Raducanu emerged victorious in straight sets over Canada's Fernandez, but at just 18 and 19-years-old respectively, the pair are now expected to dominate women's tennis and inspire millions of young girls around the world to take up the sport.

Robert Deutsch-USA TODAY Sports
